  Federation of Families for Children's Mental Health. He serves on a host of boards and volunteer agencies, including
  the St. Landry Parish Indigent Defenders Board. He is a member of Acadiana Legal Services Corporation. He attends
  Holy Ghost Catholic Church and is a member of the Advisory Board of the New Life Center (home for battered wives and
  single parents). He is a member of the St. Landry Parish Republican Executive Committee, a fellow of the Louisiana
  Bar Foundation, and an officer of the St. Landry Parish Bar Foundation. He has served as chairman of the Maryland
  Association of Human Rights Agencies, a charter member of the Urban Coalition in Norfolk, Virginia. He is also a
